    "LLMs would also be useful in marketing analytics software.",
    "However, LLMs are not equally effective at every task.",
    "LLMs struggle with SQL generation and tabular analysis, particularly involving numbers, because they were not trained specifically for these tasks.",
    "Even for use cases that focus on natural language, LLMs often suffer from the well documented hallucination problem [16][17][18], especially in cases where lengthy or domain-specific context is important.",
    "Since reliably answering domain-specific questions, writing SQL code to retrieve data, and analyzing tables is critical in a marketing analytics tool, these are important limitations."
  ],
